  "texts": [
    "We also performed our analysis with Llama-2-7B on Estonian, a low-resource language, in Fig. 21.",
    "The fact that Estonian is a low-resource language is already evident in the number of single-token words: only one out of our 99 Estonian words can be represented with a single token.",
    "In the copy task, Estonian behaves the most similarly to Chinese, with the Estonian probability exceeding the English probability already in the intermediate layers.",
    "Translation task.",
    "While the success probability on the translation task after the final layer is significantly smaller than in the languages studied in the main paper, we still observe the same effect as for the other languages: the intermediate next-token distributions decoded via the logit lens concentrate their probability mass on the correct English tokens and only in the final layers transition to Estonian."
  ],
